last_episode_to_air.name: 100th Episode
last_episode_to_air.overview: Frankie celebrates the 100th episode of Struggle Meals with a look back on memorable moments, favorite recipes, bloopers and cooking mishaps. Take a peek behind the scenes, hear from the audience, and celebrate with a special surprise guest.

name: Struggle Meals
overview: The struggle is real, but it doesnâ€™t mean your food has to suffer. Chef Frankie Celenza shows you how to make delicious meals for under $2 a plate.

episodes.name: Party for Pennies
episodes.overview: Frankie makes three dishes for a party of four, that when combined, are cheaper than just one meal out for brunch. Then, it's a taco party for five people for only $20!

episodes.name: Food Back from the Dead
episodes.overview: Stale bread, old bananas, canned food, dry foods - they often get a bad wrap, but it's not the end for them yet. Frankie shares his recipes for using these pantry staples to create delicious meals.

episodes.name: Wrap it Up!
episodes.overview: Frankie shares his method for preparing portable wraps at home for quick and easy lunches.

episodes.name: Bacon My Heart
episodes.overview: Versatility is important, and these three items - bacon, eggs, and a whole chicken - will feed you a plethora of delicious and affordable meals.

episodes.name: Instant Gratification
episodes.overview: Carbs are loved the world over. Endlessly versatile, cheap, and super filling - Frankie shares his tricks for pasta, pizza dough, and delicious, easy ramen.

episodes.name: Cauliflower's Star Power
episodes.overview: Frankie highlights the versatility of cauliflower, as well as roasts a big chuck roast that stretches over three dishes.

episodes.name: Traveling for Your Tastebuds
episodes.overview: You don't have to travel half way around the world to try a different cuisine - Frankie shows that Italian and Filipino foods are accessible right here, right now.

episodes.name: Street Food Faves at Home
episodes.overview: Frankie makes street food at home, and it's fresher, healthier, and cheaper. Then get ready, because you've never seen rice like this before.

episodes.name: Sweet on You
episodes.overview: Sweet potatoes and a sweet tooth - Frankie's got you covered on the cheap and full of nutrition. Some times, you've got to indulge.

episodes.name: Save Dough, Make Dough
episodes.overview: Prepping meals at home is cheaper and way more nutritious. Frankie makes portable breakfasts for the work week and forays into the stuffed dough of different cultures.

episodes.name: Going with the Grain
episodes.overview: Frankie teaches you how to prep ingredients to make delicious, healthy meals for a fraction of the time and cost.

episodes.name: Fancy Free
episodes.overview: Going to the movies is expensive. Frankie shows us how to make a delicious TV dinner, popcorn, and dessert, for less than the cost of a movie ticket.

episodes.name: The Chicken or the Egg
episodes.overview: Which came first? In this episode, it's the egg. Frankie shows us both high and low maintenance ways to prepare roasted chicken and eggs for any meal. Who says adulting has to be hard?

episodes.name: Frankie's Day Out
episodes.overview: Frankie shows you how to make a week's worth of meals on a single trip to the grocery store, and then shows you three options for struggle meals on the go.

episodes.name: Show Me the Mole
episodes.overview: Frankie shows you how to make delicious and filling Mexican-inspired dishes for under $2 a plate, and later uses a surprising struggle ingredient in 3 delicious dishes you'll go nuts for.

episodes.name: Potatoes Gonna Potate
episodes.overview: Who knew potatoes are not only affordable, but nutrient rich? Frankie is cookin' up 3 potato dishes that are guaranteed to fill you up, and later a trio of delicious pancakes with a surprising twist.

episodes.name: An Eggplant Extravaganza
episodes.overview: Eggplant: A fruit you didn't know was a fruit. Often underrated and overlooked, Frankie shows us how to shop for and cook this filling, delicious, cost-effective, and versatile ingredient.

episodes.name: Meat: More Bang For Your Buck
episodes.overview: It's time to reduce the cost of meat on your grocery bill. Frankie shows us which cuts of meat provide the most bang for our buck, and equally as important, how to cook them for optimal flavor.

episodes.name: Plant-Based Budget Meals
episodes.overview: Frankie busts the myth that eating plant-based is expensive. Preparing these good-for-you meals is all about eating seasonally to save money on produce, and shopping the bulk aisle for even more savings on plant-based pantry items. It's nutritious and great for the planet. Win-win!

episodes.name: The Weekly Struggle Budget
episodes.overview: Frankie figured out the weekly budget grocery equation so you don't have to. Breakfast, lunch, and dinner for seven days, for a family of four, for under $150. All it takes is a little planning, meal prep, and using up leftovers in inventive ways to avoid food waste.

episodes.name: Cheesin'
episodes.overview: Cheese can be really expensive. Frankie teaches us how to cook with more affordable cheese swaps than what might normally be called for in a recipe. More importantly, we learn how to stretch cheese in a dish so it can be the star without breaking the bank. Bonus: Frankie teaches how to make cheese at home!

episodes.name: Turn Up For Tomatoes
episodes.overview: Tomatoes are one of the most produced fruits, especially when in season. Frankie teaches us how to prepare them fresh in a variety of ways.

episodes.name: Date Night
episodes.overview: Date night doesn't have to be at an over-priced restaurant. Frankie prepares an affordable and delicious sushi date night at home, filled with three courses, plus tips on how to set date night ambiance at home on a struggle budget.

episodes.name: Lunches for Work
episodes.overview: A big way to save money on a struggle budget is to prepare homemade lunches for work. Frankie shows us how to make five delicious lunches for the whole work week. Each one flavored differently during meal prep so you don't get bored. You'll be saving money, and you might even be more productive at work after a nutritious homemade lunch!

episodes.name: Frankie & Flour
episodes.overview: Flour has the super power to transform into an endless variety of meals, and a little goes a long way. Frankie teaches us how to make three different meals using flour as the affordable vehicle.

episodes.name: Hotdishes
episodes.overview: You say hotdishes, Frankie says casserole. Either way, these one-pot hotdishes are an affordable way to feed a group of people, or the family for dinner. Plus they're great to freeze for future meals. Frankie's secret is to use a combination of frozen and fresh ingredients to keep these hotdishes nutritious and cost-effective.

episodes.name: Game Day
episodes.overview: Frankie throws a game day party for under $25. Game days aren't for dinner parties but they are a day for some fan-favorite finger foods, especially those you can make in advance.

episodes.name: Winter is Here
episodes.overview: It's the dead of winter in Frankie's kitchen, which means it's that time for hearty, delicious, and warming meals.

episodes.name: Valentine's Day
episodes.overview: Frankie prepares a Valentine's Day dinner for under $15 with a bistro-style theme to up the romance.

episodes.name: Beans Beans Beans
episodes.overview: Dried beans are the most affordable and healthy way to prepare them, with very little effort to boot. Frankie will teach the basics of preparing beans from scratch while making super tasty recipes.

episodes.name: Rent Week
episodes.overview: It's that time, the first of the month, when you spend your whole paycheck on rent and bills. Frankie cooks up some go-to pantry meals and also teaches us how to better prepare for this time of the month.

episodes.name: Mushroom Mania
episodes.overview: Frankie takes us on a magical mushroom trip. Not that kind but hey, no judgement. You may not get the trippy visions or fall in love with a tree, but mushrooms for every day meals are magical in their own special way.

episodes.name: No Kitchen No Problem
episodes.overview: Frankie teaches us a few easy and inventive "no-kitchen" hacks for delicious meals. Just because you're dorm living, road tripping, motel living, or haven't gotten that bachelor pad in shape yet, doesn't mean you can't make tasty meals.

episodes.name: Spring Fling
episodes.overview: Spring is in the air which means a whole new world opens up in the produce department, especially all the greens. Frankie does what he does best and teaches us how to cook with mother nature, spring-style.

episodes.name: Spice Is Nice
episodes.overview: Flavor, flavor, flavor. Frankie shows us the way around the spice cabinet. You know that area in your pantry that collects dust? Well get ready to dust it off.

episodes.name: Root-to-Stem
episodes.overview: Frankie teaches us how to use whole vegetables, from root-to-stem, which means no food goes to waste. Learn how to use those leafy green tops you thought were for decoration.

episodes.name: Holiday Flavors
episodes.overview: The holiday season looks different this year, so why not mix things up and celebrate classic flavors in new and unexpected ways. Frankie puts a twist on all your holiday favorites, using simple ingredients for your loved ones to enjoy.

episodes.name: Less Stress Holidays
episodes.overview: The holidays are hectic enough, and with more planning, cooking and cleaning than usual, everyone wants to shop smart and save time. Frankie tackles weekday meals that will keep you organized, fed, and less stressed this season.

episodes.name: Warm + Cozy Winter
episodes.overview: Frankie gets cozy with recipes that bring warmth, flavor and joy to the kitchen on the coldest winter days.

episodes.name: Eggscellent Techniques
episodes.overview: Learn Frankie's techniques and tricks for making your favorite egg dishes just the way you like them.

episodes.name: Vintage
episodes.overview: Frankie shows us that vintage doesn't have to break the bank with these classic, oldie-but-goodie recipes.

episodes.name: Struggle Soup
episodes.overview: Follow Frankie's blueprint for building a hit soup, and you'll be singing for seconds all year round.

episodes.name: Struggle Sandwich
episodes.overview: Every layer counts as Frankie ups the ante on classic sandwiches, with homemade twists that steal the show.

episodes.name: Cabbage, Cabbage, Cabbage
episodes.overview: Cabbage has never been cooler than right now, proving to be the utility ingredient we never knew we needed.

episodes.name: Mayo: The Secret Ingredient
episodes.overview: Frankie unlocks mayo's secret powers that take your recipes to the next level, all without leaving a trace.

episodes.name: Crunchy
episodes.overview: There's nothing like a satisfying crunch to up your recipe game; bonus points for not bursting your budget.

episodes.name: A Cruciferous Delicious Time
episodes.overview: No veggie family stands the test of time like the cruciferous family, and its hearty meals will win you over

episodes.name: 5-Ingredient Recipes
episodes.overview: Less is more when it comes to simple weeknight meals that focus on maximum flavor and minimal ingredients.

episodes.name: Summer BBQ
episodes.overview: Summer is coming to a close but there's still a bounty of fresh, seasonal produce to enjoy. Celebrate with Frankie as he makes some of his favorite cookout classics that'll take you from a weekend picnic to a backyard BBQ, with or without a grill.

episodes.name: Bring Your Own Lunch
episodes.overview: Frankie is all about BYOL - bring your own lunch. It's not only good for your wallet, it's good for your health. Skip the vending machine and the cafeteria in favor of creative, cost effective and easy-to-transport midday meals.

episodes.name: Salad Salad Salad
episodes.overview: Amp up your salad game with a little mixing and matching, from light and leafy greens to crisp and hearty toppings, and dressings for all occasions. Frankie shows us how versatile and fulfilling a homemade salad can truly be.

episodes.name: How Do You Like Them Apples
episodes.overview: Apples aren't just good for keeping the doctor away. Frankie demonstrates how to make the most of this beloved, everyday fruit, from sweet treats to savory meals. There's a whole world of apples to dive into, especially while they're in season.

episodes.name: Super Squash
episodes.overview: Never underestimate the power of squash: they're affordable, abundant and they come in all shapes, sizes, colors, and textures. Frankie spotlights squash from summer through winter highlighting their amazing superhero traits.

episodes.name: Spooktacular Tricks and Treats
episodes.overview: Don't let the line of trick-or-treaters or the candy corn overload scare you out of the kitchen this Halloween. Frankie's got tricks up his sleeve to make simple yet wicked good treats for everyone at the party to enjoy. All while saving some dough.

episodes.name: Let's Play Ball
episodes.overview: Batter up! Fall ball is heating up, and Frankie's offering us his favorite stadium snacks, without those major league prices. No matter who you're rooting for, these ballpark classics will be a hit with friends and family for seasons to come.

episodes.name: The Future is Flavor
episodes.overview: Frankie harnesses the power of time to transform simple ingredients into flavorful goods that'll stick around for a long time. Learn the basics of preserving, pickling & curing to make dinner anything but a struggle. It just takes a little patience.

episodes.name: Pantry Pasta
episodes.overview: Keep your pantry stocked with a few basic staples, and you'll always have ingredients on hand for dinner, especially for pasta night. In this episode, Frankie creates delicious pasta dishes with the kitchen's best-kept secret weapon - the pantry.

episodes.name: Potato Variety Show
episodes.overview: Today, Frankie's slicing, mashing and smashing his way through the spud species, an essential staple for any Struggle kitchen. They've got so many talents and textures that whichever way you dig 'em, potatoes will never let you down.

episodes.name: Citrus Sunshine
episodes.overview: Winter citrus is here to brighten up your day. Frankie is fixing up some light, zesty, and affordable recipes to add a little seasonal sunshine to your plate.

episodes.name: Suppertime Superstar
episodes.overview: Whether youâ€™re cooking for a casual weeknight or a special occasion, Frankie shared delicious and hearty dishes that will not only shine on the dinner table, but theyâ€™ll also impress your guests, without costing an arm and a leg.

episodes.name: A Leftover Glowup
episodes.overview: Give last weekâ€™s leftovers the makeover they deserve with Frankieâ€™s recipes for tasty, waste-reducing meals that transform uninspiring excess food into fresh and exciting dishes. Your bank account will thank you.

episodes.name: Romantic Steakhouse Dinner
episodes.overview: Give your wallet a break by taking the fine-dining experience straight to the comfort of your home. From tender, juicy steak paired with classic sides, to decadent desserts, Frankie's got your date night meal covered.

episodes.name: Fancy Pants Pasta
episodes.overview: This week, treat yourself to a restaurant-worthy pasta dinner at a fraction of the price, as Frankie cooks up some of his signature dishes featuring show stopping sauces.

episodes.name: I Need To Eat Right Now
episodes.overview: At the end of a long, hectic day, when you need dinner in a pinch, Frankie unlocks his not-so-secret formula for whipping up quick and easy meals, using minimal ingredients that will satisfy your cravings and feed the family in a flash.

episodes.name: Piece Of The Pie
episodes.overview: There may be infinite ways to define pie, but the only math that matters is what makes these sweet and savory dishes fit the bill. In true Struggle Style, Frankie rolls out his best tips and tricks for enjoying hassle free, cost friendly pies.

episodes.name: The Big Game
episodes.overview: Brackets are complete and all thatâ€™s missing is food to fuel your teamâ€™s run. Huddle around the kitchen as Frankie preps the ultimate watch party spread. These savory, spicy and sweet dishes are championship-worthy even if your bracket goes bust.

episodes.name: Bananas For Bananas
episodes.overview: As one of the cheapest members of the produce aisle, bananas will save you bunches of money when you whip up these delightfully appealing recipes that go above and beyond a basic bread.

episodes.name: Cry Me An Allium River
episodes.overview: Frankie takes on his longtime frenemy, the onion, and all its powerful relatives. There might be a few tears shed along the way, but they are well worth the delicious and flavorful results, from sweet buttery leeks to the ultimate onion masterpiece.

episodes.name: Pizza My Heart
episodes.overview: On this special delivery episode of Struggle Meals, Frankie explores three ways to make delicious pizzas, and shares clever tips to make an A+ pie without dropping your dough on expensive ingredients.

episodes.name: French Bistro
episodes.overview: Bonsoir, indeed! Join Frankie as he cooks up elegant but achievable French classics that will transport you to an evening on the Seine, complete with some savvy wine tips without the hefty cost of a plane ticket.

episodes.name: Thanksgiving Dinner
episodes.overview: Thanksgiving dinner will be a breeze this year thanks to Frankie's struggle tips for a delicious holiday meal. From a simple turkey entree to a new twist on a classic dessert, Frankie makes a feast without unstuffing his wallet.

episodes.name: Meatless Mains
episodes.overview: Start a new tradition at the dinner table this year with a meat free spin on your favorite main courses. Learn new tips and tricks to make your veggie forward dinner so delightful that even the biggest meat eaters will be back for seconds.

episodes.name: Spice Spice Baby
episodes.overview: Frankie kicks it up a notch in the Struggle Kitchen with flavor-packed, spicy recipes, and some hot tips for adding layers of flavor. But don't sweat it, these warming dishes won't burn your cash or your tastebuds.

episodes.name: Easy Meals For A Crowd
episodes.overview: Finicky family coming to town? Fear not, for Frankie's sharing all the struggle tips and tricks to keep the stress levels low and the enjoyment high with simple, delicious meals to please everyone at the table.

episodes.name: Holiday Sweet Treats
episodes.overview: 'Tis the jolly season of giving, but this year, there will be no more struggles in making your list and checking it twice. Frankie's festive, budget-friendly treats are the sweetest way to tell your friends and family you love them.

episodes.name: Homemade for the Holidays
episodes.overview: There's no better way to spread some holiday spirit than at the dinner table with these decadent, festive recipes that can make any long, dark night feel warm and merry.

episodes.name: Chinese Take Out
episodes.overview: With the help of a friend, Frankie serves up easy and delicious recipes based on take out favorites everyone will enjoy at home. No need to shell out extra cash for delivery fees!

episodes.name: New Years Party
episodes.overview: Wow your party guests this New Years Eve by serving these fancy but frugal dishes to ring in the year right. From appetizers to mocktails, everyone will enjoy your spread!

episodes.name: One Pot Meals
episodes.overview: Any true struggle cook knows there's nothing better than a one pot dinner. Not only is there hardly any cleanup at the end, but the prep is minimal too, which means hunger satisfaction is imminent. Who says meals can't be cheap, easy and delicious?

episodes.name: Homemade-ish
episodes.overview: Last minute company leaving you in a pinch? Frankie has you covered with these easy recipes featuring store bought staples. With a few Struggle tips, these basic ingredients can be transformed into dishes that will impress your guests.

episodes.name: Eat Your Greens
episodes.overview: Going green isn't just a trend; it's a no-brainer! When the veggies are in season and the prices are at their lowest, Frankie's colorful recipes and zero waste tips will have you celebrating the savings with fresh spring produce.

episodes.name: Between Two Buns
episodes.overview: Is it a burger? Is it a sandwich? Is a burger a sandwich? Not even Frankie knows the answer, but one thing is certain: whatever you want to call them, these fun twists and familiar flavor combos are super satisfying to scarf down.

episodes.name: Struggle Splurge
episodes.overview: The key to treating yourself on a budget is to keep it simple: these elegant dinners taste like restaurant specials, but they can be prepared in under one hour - perfect for easy weeknight meals for a family of any size on a busy schedule.

episodes.name: But First, Brunch
episodes.overview: Bring your loved ones together over a delicious brunch spread made with love. Whether you're celebrating a major milestone or simply toasting to the weekend, Frankie's money-saving menu will have guests buzzing for more.

episodes.name: Saved By The Bowl
episodes.overview: When you're craving a quick nutritious meal, say no more to throwing cash down the gutter for overpriced takeout bowls! Frankie recreates three restaurant favorites for a fraction of the cost, sparing your bank account without sacrificing flavor.

episodes.name: Summer Cookout
episodes.overview: Soak up summer with the ultimate outdoor cookout, featuring smashburgers, pasta salad and scrumptious sweets. These classic dishes can be prepared indoors or out, making them the perfect recipes for backyard dinner parties on warm summer nights.

episodes.name: Picnic Lunches
episodes.overview: It's field trip day, and Frankie shows off his best handheld lunches perfect for leisurely days at the park, the beach or the pool. These sturdy meals are made to travel and only get better with time.

episodes.name: Too Hot To Cook
episodes.overview: When the temps are soaring and turning on your stove or oven is not even an option, Frankie's no cook meals will blow you away. Enjoy refreshing, nourishing dishes that will help keep you cool all summer long.

episodes.name: Christmas In July
episodes.overview: It's July on the calendar but Christmas in our hearts. Frankie whips up three summertime twists on Christmas themed dishes and serves up tips and tricks for celebrating the most wonderful time of year in July.

episodes.name: We Knead Pizza
episodes.overview: Cancel the pizza delivery, it's time to save money and build your pies from scratch. With three different pizza styles, you're bound to find one that satisfies your craving without digging into your wallet.

episodes.name: Oktoberfest
episodes.overview: Join Frankie as he shares his budget friendly takes on Oktoberfest-inspired dishes, perfect for celebrating the fall season with friends. These festive and hearty meals will keep you cosy and full, and best of all, pair nicely with a beer.

episodes.name: Sweater Weather
episodes.overview: The air is crisp and the leaves are changing, which means it's time to gather 'round the dinner table for hearty, seasonal meals on a budget. These warm dishes are sure to keep you cozy all season long.

episodes.name: Happy Halloween
episodes.overview: Boo! It's spooky season, and what better way to get into the spirit than with affordable, party-friendly Halloween dishes that scream trick or treat?! But be warned, these meals are scary good.

episodes.name: Whole Chicken 101
episodes.overview: Join Frankie to learn the ins and outs of using every part of a chicken, as he demonstrates how to maximize the value and minimize waste. By cooking smarter, you'll have three delectable recipes to last you the whole week.

episodes.name: Frankie's Italian Faves
episodes.overview: Everyone knows Frankie can't live without pasta, but this week he shares his favorite Italian recipes that don't require any kneading. Add these simple, delicious dishes to your weeknight menu to complete your Italian dish repertoire.

episodes.name: Meals Under $7
episodes.overview: At a loss when your pantry is empty? With these recipes, you can walk into any grocery store with only $7 and walk out with everything you need for an entire meal. Because yes, you can whip up a nutritious meal at an affordable price!

episodes.name: Grubby Good Food
episodes.overview: Send your taste buds on a first class food tour without even leaving the Struggle kitchen! Frankie whips up his favorite regional specialties from five destinations, making them as authentic as possible while sticking to his budget.

episodes.name: Thanksgiving Leftovers
episodes.overview: Give Thanksgiving leftovers a whole new meaning this year. Frankie knows just the trick for transforming turkey day dishes into totally new flavors. With recipes this good, youâ€™ll be twice as full and endlessly more thankful.

episodes.name: Breakfast for Dinner
episodes.overview: It's dinnertime and breakfast is on the menu this week. These affordable breakfast specials are hearty enough for dinner, and so delicious they may even taste better after dark. Grab a fork and dig in for the most important meal of the day!

episodes.name: 100th Episode
episodes.overview: Frankie celebrates the 100th episode of Struggle Meals with a look back on memorable moments, favorite recipes, bloopers and cooking mishaps. Take a peek behind the scenes, hear from the audience, and celebrate with a special surprise guest.
